char arctic20_transcription[] = "<s> AUTHOR OF THE DANGER TRAIL PHILIP STEELS ETC </s> (arctic_0001)\x0A<s> NOT AT THIS PARTICULAR CASE TOM APOLOGIZED WHITTEMORE </s> (arctic_0002)\x0A<s> FOR THE TWENTIETH TIME THAT EVENING THE TWO MEN SHOOK HANDS </s> (arctic_0003)\x0A<s> LORD BUT I'M GLAD TO SEE YOU AGAIN PHIL </s> (arctic_0004)\x0A<s> WILL WE EVER FORGET IT </s> (arctic_0005)\x0A<s> GOD BLESS 'EM I HOPE I'LL GO ON SEEING THEM FOREVER </s> (arctic_0006)\x0A<s> AND YOU ALWAYS WANT TO SEE IT IN THE SUPERLATIVE DEGREE </s> (arctic_0007)\x0A<s> GAD YOUR LETTER CAME JUST IN TIME </s> (arctic_0008)\x0A<s> HE TURNED SHARPLY AND FACED GREGSON ACROSS THE TABLE </s> (arctic_0009)\x0A<s> I'M PLAYING A SINGLE HAND IN WHAT LOOKS LIKE A LOSING GAME </s> (arctic_0010)\x0A<s> IF I EVER NEEDED A FIGHTER IN MY LIFE I NEED ONE NOW </s> (arctic_0011)\x0A<s> GREGSON SHOVED BACK HIS CHAIR AND ROSE TO HIS FEET </s> (arctic_0012)\x0A<s> HE WAS A HEAD SHORTER THAN HIS COMPANION OF ALMOST DELICATE PHYSIQUE </s> (arctic_0013)\x0A<s> NOW YOU'RE COMING DOWN TO BUSINESS PHIL HE EXCLAIMED </s> (arctic_0014)\x0A<s> IT'S THE AURORA BOREALIS </s> (arctic_0015)\x0A<s> THERE'S FORT CHURCHILL A RIFLESHOT BEYOND THE RIDGE ASLEEP </s> (arctic_0016)\x0A<s> FROM THAT MOMENT HIS FRIENDSHIP FOR BELIZE TURNS TO HATRED AND JEALOUSY </s> (arctic_0017)\x0A<s> THERE WAS A CHANGE NOW </s> (arctic_0018)\x0A<s> I FOLLOWED THE LINE OF THE PROPOSED RAILROAD LOOKING FOR CHANCES </s> (arctic_0019)\x0A<s> CLUBS AND BALLS AND CITIES GREW TO BE ONLY MEMORIES </s> (arctic_0020)\x0A";

char arctic20_txt[] = "Author of the danger trail, Philip Steels, etc.\x0ANot at this particular case, Tom, apologized Whittemore.\x0AFor the twentieth time that evening the two men shook hands.\x0ALord, but I'm glad to see you again, Phil.\x0AWill we ever forget it.\x0AGod bless 'em, I hope I'll go on seeing them forever.\x0AAnd you always want to see it in the superlative degree.\x0AGad, your letter came just in time.\x0AHe turned sharply, and faced Gregson across the table.\x0AI'm playing a single hand in what looks like a losing game.\x0AIf I ever needed a fighter in my life I need one now.\x0AGregson shoved back his chair and rose to his feet.\x0AHe was a head shorter than his companion, of almost delicate physique.\x0ANow you're coming down to business, Phil, he exclaimed.\x0AIt's the aurora borealis.\x0AThere's Fort Churchill, a rifle-shot beyond the ridge, asleep.\x0AFrom that moment his friendship for Belize turns to hatred and jealousy.\x0AThere was a change now.\x0AI followed the line of the proposed railroad, looking for chances.\x0AClubs and balls and cities grew to be only memories.\x0A";

